  "text": "Water pollution caused by organic pollutants (i.e., herbicides, pesticides, pharmaceuticals and care products) is a major problem which should be faced. Some hydrophobic organic compounds could accumulate in oil or similar mediums in which they are very stable and could cause public health problems [CITATION_1] . Therefore, their elimination needs great efforts. In recent years, the production and application of herbicides and pesticides have been changed; polar and more easily degraded ones have been replaced by nonpolar and stable ones [CITATION_2] .",
